'''''Photographie.com''''' is the oldest [[France|French]] photography [[online magazine]].<ref>[http://photo.sohu.com/20110422/n280378317.shtml Didier de Fays和Photographie.com] (in English/Chinese)</ref> The subscription-free magazine includes all genres of photography and contains exhibition and photo book reviews, essays, analysis and criticism about photography and culture.<ref name="Art">{{Cite news|author=Raphaëlle Stopin|title=Premier lustre pour Photographie.com|date=17 January 2002|work=Art Aujourd'hui|url =http://www.artaujourdhui.info/q1386-premier-lustre-pour-photographie-com.html|accessdate=21 November 2012|language=French}}</ref> It also provides video interviews with photographers, curators and other photography experts.
==History and profile== Photographie.com was created in 1996 by Jean-François Bauret, Yan Morvan and Didier de Faÿs to advance the interests of photographers and quickly established itself as a trusted name in photography.<ref name="Art"/> In 1998 Photographie.com launched the ''Bourse du Talent'' photography competition which awards prizes to young photographers in four different categories: reportage, portrait, fashion and landscape.<ref>[http://www.artcatalyse.fr/52eme-bourse-du-talent-photographie-com.html ArtCatalyse].</ref> The work of the prize winners is exhibited at the [[Bibliothèque nationale de France]] every year.<ref name="BnF">{{Cite news|author=Mathias Depardon|title=Jeunes photographes de la Bourse du Talent|date = 30 December 2011|work=Bibliothèque nationale de France|url =http://www.bnf.fr/fr/evenements_et_culture/anx_expositions/f.bourse_talent_11.html|accessdate=21 November 2012|language=French }}</ref>
